<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-310-958  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 310 958.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  May 29 1989 n419 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM Telecom platform on the skids.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Duffy, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM has reportedly abandoned its plan to build a service controlpoint (SCP) platform and has opted to support othertelecommunications companies in establishing a standard platformfor telephone equipment.andP;  Service control point platforms includea computer and a switch to provide improved telephone services.andO;The Multiple Vendor Interaction Group is establishing standardsfor such devices.andP;  The group, made of Bell operating companies andswitch vendors, has commissioned Bell Communications Research todevelop a common platform.andP;  The platform will allow variouscomponents of an intelligent phone network to operate togethereven if made by different companies.andP;  An architecture is expectedto be defined by 1995.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Telephone SystemsTelephone CompaniesProduct FailuresBell Regional Holding CompaniesTrade and Professional AssociationsStandardsMarketing StrategyMultiple Vendor Interaction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>